content:
This was initially just testing out my reconfigured setup&hellip; but figured I&rsquo;d run with it.
https://youtu.be/L3tj2vKJC_c
This doesn&rsquo;t mean I&rsquo;m abandoning the configuration I am working on for getting multiple tracks together, just that I was getting some more concepts together :D Nothing technically I haven&rsquo;t done before, but this is all tracks that I played out, tweaked notes, velocity and all that fun stuff, to try and get a sound I was going for. Hopefully the levels are working better&hellip;

Just a track made in Koala Sampler from an auto chopped found sound&hellip;
https://soundcloud.com/neartao/beatober2021-11-fancy-towel?si=ed4b3b3b61e040c59fa635d5792e7f16
The track is definitely missing some parts (like uh&hellip; bass), that I&rsquo;d normally put in there&hellip; but I only really had about 30 minutes to flesh something out and this was pretty fun to just scrub through and see what would and would not work. With more time I am sure I could find all kinds of cool sounds&hellip; but Koala Sampler only has 64 (well 63 due to needing to have a starting sample) slots to fill&hellip; and I could see scrubbing through by hand being a better result, but auto chopping served me well enough here to go through it&hellip; so there is that.
Thing is&hellip; I have a *ton* of found sound material, and keep meaning to load it into something&hellip; Koala, MPC, Morphagene, guess it is time to get off my but and make something proper with all this material. Biggest problem is probably wind&hellip; but there&rsquo;s not a crazy amount of wind&hellip;

Man&hellip; the MPC Live mk2 rarely crashes on me&hellip; and lost some work&hellip; I suspect I know what I did&hellip; but *sigh*&hellip; anyways&hellip; regrouped and did this&hellip;
https://soundcloud.com/neartao/new-paint
The picture is just one of my watercolor paint sets&hellip; almost went with a rain motif instead&hellip; boy is it raining out right now!

Just something quick for the day&hellip;
https://soundcloud.com/neartao/low-status
Long day&hellip; doing work around the house&hellip; not really feeling writing up much else today&hellip; catch ya tomorrow!

Word&hellip;
https://soundcloud.com/neartao/lambic-eight
So I just used the picture from a website&hellip; sue me&hellip; well don&rsquo;t&hellip; but I didn&rsquo;t happen to have eight lambic around to photograph&hellip;
This is yet another track in the vaporwave style&hellip; or rather&hellip; dumping some loops/sounds into the SP-202 and making something pitched down&hellip; I&rsquo;m probably abusing this too much by now for making a track a day for the month&hellip; but hey&hellip; if it works? Keep on filtering? Keep on trying out the new synths on the MPC from 2.10? I mean heck yeah!
So I&rsquo;m still learning some of the new 2.10 features, but definitely planning on moving back to the Eurorack setup soon, I actually have all of the remaining&hellip; non case modification parts arriving soon, so definitely going to get that set back up, and figure out if/how to incorporate the SPs into the workflow.

https://soundcloud.com/neartao/some-class
The picture is from my daughter playing piano for a recital. It was&hellip; three years ago now? She&rsquo;s been learning to play piano for five or six years now, and knows far more about playing music than I do. She can sight read, has very good finger posture, and knows her way around the keys. On the other hand, I try and talk to her about sampling, beat making, song structure, and these are things she doesn&rsquo;t know how to do. Occasionally we will talk and bounce ideas off of each other, but she&rsquo;s not into creating songs, just more interested in reproducing them right now.
To put the track together&hellip; I just kind of felt like doing an orchestral hip hop track&hellip; so it&rsquo;s some timpani, cello, viola, and other orchestral sounds&hellip; and just some rather basic hip hop drums and a few other sounds to try and round out the track a bit. I took another pass at making the track 64 bars, and then messing around with track mutes to put the track together. This is both a bit faster, and a bit slower than making sequences, and stringing them together in a song. It&rsquo;s faster because if you can get it right or sounding decent out of the gate you don&rsquo;t have to fiddle with it too much&hellip; but it is also slower because if you mess up you then have to decide if you&rsquo;re going to go into list edit to fix your timing up or if you&rsquo;re going to undo but then have to redo everything&hellip; you can somewhat get around this by turning overdub on and off between track mute change ups&hellip; but that&rsquo;s one more thing to remember to do&hellip;

For day 27&hellip; I missed the mark&hellip;
https://soundcloud.com/neartao/broken-garage
So not really a garage&hellip; but boy was that toy for my daughter busted. I ended up upgrading it with a bunch of additions like a tiny and working tv inside, fixed up the doorbell, it was a pretty rocking little house. When we got it though, it was broken as heck&hellip;
Kind of like the song I put together. I was kind of thinking about going for a House track&hellip; and as you listen to it you can tell I kind of split between an acid baseline, and some other sounds in there&hellip; and never really committed to a garage track, or a UK track&hellip; or anything else. It straddles the line, but not in a good way. I suspect I need to burn this track with fire&hellip; but today I had been working on two or three other tracks to started out with&hellip; and just never was happy with anything. I guess not every day can be decent or above.

Twenty Eight Songs In A Row&hellip; woah&hellip;
https://soundcloud.com/neartao/catch-of-the-day
I&rsquo;m not going to lie to you folks&hellip;
This has been a lot of back to back to back tracks for me, and I am kind of looking forward to the month ending so I can get into a different musical head space. This was just a straight up Expansion Pack kit that I loaded up, and then added a bit more to it with some samples from my brand spanking new Waldorf Iridium. I was more into just playing with the Iridium than making a track, but figured I needed to get moving and actually put something together.
To do something completely different&hellip; I tried to make a straight up 32 bar track, and then just add/remove content instead of messing with mutes and all. It felt different, though I am not sure that I am actually happy with how it worked for me. Probably a process that could be figured out for me, but it made things feel wonky. So *shrug*&hellip; at least I tried something new, even if it didn&rsquo;t work the way I wanted.
